methods.accept:
Deliver a single range. Methods receiving a RangeConsumer should call accept on it for non-empty, disjoint
 ranges. Calls should be made in increasing order of values contained in the ranges.

:param begin: (int) - first value of the range to add.
:param end: (int) - one past the last value in the range to add (ie, end is exclusive).
:return: (boolean) false if no more ranges are desired, true otherwise.

text: Results comprised of multiple, ordered ranges are provided via this interface.
